# UI icons & brand imagery

## Prefer vector over raster

Use **SVG** (inline in React, or a `.svg` file under `public/`) whenever the
asset is geometric / brand / chrome. Prefer **inline SVG in React** for UI
chrome. Do **not** ship PNG/JPEG/WebP for logos or icons unless a platform
requires raster (favicon ICO/PNG sizes, apple-touch, PWA maskable, photos,
user avatars).

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — chrome icon as inline SVG
<svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
  <path d="…" stroke="currentColor" strokeWidth="2" strokeLinecap="round" />
</svg>

// ✅ GOOD — brand mark as SVG file
<img src="/logo-mark-light.svg" alt="" width={28} height={28} />

// ❌ BAD — raster logo/icon when a vector exists or can be used
<img src="/logo-mark-light.png" alt="" />
<img src="/icon-edit.png" alt="" />
```

## Brand mark & wordmark

- Mark files: `public/logo-mark-light.svg` (Floral + Pumpkin),
  `public/logo-mark-dark.svg` (Black + Pumpkin). Canonical source for chrome.
- Wordmark in UI is **text** (`BrandWordmark` / `BrandFullLogo` lockup) — not an
  image.
- Do **not** keep unused `logo-full-*.png` or other raster logos “just in case”.

After changing `logo-mark-light.svg`, run `npm run icons:regen` (writes
`favicon.svg` + raster favicon/PWA derivatives that platforms require).

## When `public/` is appropriate

Put files under `public/` **only** for:

- Brand mark SVGs (`logo-mark-light.svg`, `logo-mark-dark.svg`) and favicon.svg
- Platform-required raster derivatives (`favicon-*.png`, `favicon.ico`,
  `apple-touch-icon.png`, `icon-192` / `icon-512`, maskable)
- Avatars (`avatar-default.png` and user-uploaded/served avatars)
- Icons that must be shared as files (e.g. CSS `mask-image` →
  `icon-theme-auto.svg`)

Name new static icons `public/icon-<purpose>.svg` (prefer) or `.png` only when
raster is required, and **reference them from code** in the same change. Do not
leave unreferenced files in `public/`.

## User-provided assets

If the user supplies an icon file, use it **byte-identical**. Do **not** invent,
redraw, “improve,” or AI-generate a replacement.

## Cleanup

Do **not** keep unused generated or legacy UI icons in `public/` (e.g. old
`icon-edit.png`, `icon-cancel.png`, `icon-verified.png`,
`icon-channel-connected.png`, `icon-channel-disconnected.png`,
`icon-calendar.png`, orphaned `logo-*.png` once unreferenced).
When chrome moves to inline/vector SVG, delete the orphaned raster in the same
change.
